classifiers: Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules
info.description:
Example usage::

        import pyfatcache

        conn = pyfatcache.get_conn()
        conn.delete("a")
        print "expect (None, None) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
        conn.set("a", "a", flags=1)
        print "expect ('a', 1) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
        conn.set("a", dict(name="pyfatcache"))
        print "expect ({'name': 'pyfatcache'}, 0) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
        conn.set("a", None)
        print "expect (None, 0) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
        conn.close()
info.name: pyfatcache
info.summary: a simple python client for twitter's fatcache
info.html_description:
Example usage:

import pyfatcache

conn = pyfatcache.get_conn()
conn.delete("a")
print "expect (None, None) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
conn.set("a", "a", flags=1)
print "expect ('a', 1) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
conn.set("a", dict(name="pyfatcache"))
print "expect ({'name': 'pyfatcache'}, 0) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
conn.set("a", None)
print "expect (None, 0) / get %s" % (str(conn.get("a")),)
conn.close()
